The <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> claims its ministerial positions, with Adam Stegerwald securing the Labor Ministry, and other members taking the Transport and Justice portfolios. The <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> also brings the <span style="color: #A2D8E0;">**BVP**</span> into the fold, which is granted the Postal Ministry.

With Ludwig Kaas’s connections in Rome, the negotiation of a <i>Reichskonkordat</i> is fast-tracked and set to be ready for signing in a few weeks.

However, their entry into government has strained our relations, as they had previously stood in united opposition with us.